IFN-gamma secretion is observed upon culture with this peptide of PBMC from 4 out of 15 BCG-vaccinated healthy donors and from 6 out of 7 TB patients, suggesting it is immunodominant.An 89% sequence identity is found with a peptide from PPE family protein Rv3021c (aa 45-62) present in both M. tuberculosis and M. bovis (Table 1) and a similar degree of homology is found with several Mycobaterium species protein regions (Table 2). This protein is shown to be expressed in the cell wall or cell membrane. It is encoded by an ORF located in region RD1, the first region deleted in M. Bovis during BCG vaccine propagation. Nevertheless, it is recognized by some BCG vaccinated, non-TB exposed individuals, by means of cross reactive epitopes.
